ğŸ‘‰ These keys are like â€œprogrammatic credentialsâ€ that allow tools (Terraform, AWS CLI, SDKs, etc.) to act on your AWS account without logging in through the web.

Access Key ID â†’ like a username

Secret Access Key â†’ like a password

Terraform uses these keys to authenticate itself to AWS whenever it tries to:

Create a VPC

Launch EC2 instances

Create RDS databases

Manage IAM, S3, etc.

ğŸ” Without these keys, Terraform has no way to â€œproveâ€ to AWS who is making the request â†’ AWS rejects the operation.

âš¡ Example

If you run:

