single_nat_gateway = true

By default, Terraform can create one NAT Gateway per availability zone for high availability.

Setting single_nat_gateway = true tells Terraform to create only one NAT Gateway and share it across all private subnets.
âœ… Purpose:

Save cost â€” only one NAT Gateway (billed hourly) instead of multiple.

âš ï¸ Trade-off:
If that one NAT Gateway fails or the AZ itâ€™s in goes down, all private subnets lose internet access.

ğŸ’¡ Use in learning/testing â†’ âœ…
ğŸ’¡ Use in production â†’ âŒ (better to have one NAT per AZ)



